definitions: To arise or appear, especially unexpectedly.
To travel from a more southerly place to a more northerly place.
To reach a higher level or position.
examples: A new issue came up in the meeting.
He came up to me and asked for directions.
The sun came up early this morning.
I hope nothing urgent comes up.
She's coming up from Florida next week.
He's trying to come up in the company.
